      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here are a few options for a rejection email, but I've kept them suitably polished for a senior role. Remember to tailor the bracketed sections, of course. It's important to be respectful, even when the candidate is a high-level prospect, and you don't want them to feel like they were just a pile of rejects in a pile of other rejects.\n\n***\n\n**Option 1: Warm and Appreciative**\n\nSubject: Update on the Senior Developer Position at [Company Name]\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you so much for taking the time to interview for the Senior Developer position. We truly enjoyed getting to know you and learning more about your impressive background. The final round was incredibly competitive, and we were genuinely impressed by your skills and experience. We have decided to move forward with another candidate whose specific experience aligned slightly closer to our immediate needs for this particular role.\n\nThis was a difficult decision, as you are a very strong candidate. We wish you the absolute best in your job search and future endeavors. We hope our paths may cross again in the future!\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n\n***\n\n**Option 2: More Direct and Concise**\n\nSubject:",
