      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here is Option 2, finished and incorporating the nuance you requested. It's professional, but honestly, it feels a bit like a carefully worded negotiation with a very smart, slightly grumpy, but ultimately fair, middle manager—which is kind of how I feel about these things, honestly.\n\n***\n\n**Option 2: More Direct and Concise (Revised)**\n\nSubject: Update on the Senior Developer Position at [Company Name]\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you again for investing your time in the final stages of our interview process for the Senior Developer role. We want to emphasize that your technical skills and problem-solving abilities are genuinely outstanding. It was a truly difficult decision, as we interviewed several exceptional individuals. Ultimately, we have decided to move forward with a candidate whose background offered a more direct, immediate depth of experience specifically within large-scale cloud architecture, which is a critical focus for us right now.\n\nPlease know this decision reflects the specific needs of this role at this moment, and not a reflection of your overall talent. We sincerely appreciate your interest in [Company Name] and wish you the very best in finding a role that is the perfect fit for your talents.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]",
